text: The Good, the Bad, the UglyDiscography is the debut studio album by American recording artist Frankee, released in 2004. Her debut single "F.U.R.B." is an answer song to Eamon's "Fuck It (I Don't Want You Back)". To date it is the only album released by Frankee. ==Track listing== #"I Do Me" #"How You Do" #"In Love with Me" #"I'm Leaving" #"Gotta Man" #"Who the Hell Are You" #"Him" #"I Told You So" #"Hell No" #"Don't Be Mad" #"F.U.R.B.
